ource_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":1},"text_hash":"24d57bb637428607f5abfe1328896a5079f57131"},{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../gill/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":2}}],"20":[{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../pulpit/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"pulpit","source_name":"Pulpit Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":20}},{"match":"hash","source_href":"../../mhc/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"mhc","source_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":14},"text_hash":"1fd3ba4287f88acc7f01884a9490fe615a6f31ae"},{"commentary_html":"At that time I will bring you again, even in the time that I gather you,.... That is, at the time that the Lord will gather them in the effectual calling to himself and to his church, he will return them to their own land; and, as soon as the Jews are converted, they will not only be gathered into Christian churches, but will be gathered together in one body, and appoint themselves one head; and will go up out of each of the lands wherein they have been dispersed, and enter into their own land, and possess it; at the same time they are made partakers of the grace of God, they will enjoy all their civil privileges and liberties; see <a href=\"../../chapter/hosea/1-11.htm\">Hosea 1:11</a>, <p>for I will make you a name and a praise among all people of the earth; this is repeated from the preceding verse <a href=\"../../chapter/zephaniah/3-19.htm\">Zephaniah 3:19</a>, for the confirmation of it; and in connection with the following clause, to show when it will be: <p>when I turn back your captivity before your eyes, saith the Lord; or \"captivities\" (x); meaning not the several captivities of the kings of Judah in Babylon, as of Manasseh, Jehoiakim, Jeconiah, and Zedekiah; but the two fold captivity of this people, literal and spiritual; their present outward exile from their own land, captivity and dispersion among the nations; and their spiritual captivity or bondage, to sin, Satan, the law, and the traditions of their elders; from both which they will be delivered at one and the same time; and which will be notorious and manifest; what their eyes will see with pleasure and admiration; and which may he depended upon will be done, since the Lord has said it, whose purposes, promises, and prophecies, never fail of their accomplishment: he is God omniscient and knows with certainty what will be done; he is God omnipotent, and can and will do whatever he has determined, promised, or said should be done. <p>(x) \"captivitates vestras\", Pagninus, Montanus, Calvin, Drusius.","content_hash":"d626e2f9358c86b4e3a8c13fac6bb9267677b56c","links":[{"book_id":"hosea","chapter":1,"href":"../../chapter/hosea/1-11.htm","label":"Hosea 1:11","verse_end":11,"verse_start":11},{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"href":"../../chapter/zephaniah/3-19.htm","label":"Zephaniah 3:19","verse_end":19,"verse_start":19}],"source_href":"../../gill/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","text_hash":"50b438e24c52421cec274e624ace10e6d714be75"}],"3":[{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../pulpit/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"pulpit","source_name":"Pulpit Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":3}},{"match":"hash","source_href":"../../mhc/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"mhc","source_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":1},"text_hash":"24d57bb637428607f5abfe1328896a5079f57131"},{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../gill/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":3}}],"4":[{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../pulpit/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"pulpit","source_name":"Pulpit Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":4}},{"match":"hash","source_href":"../../mhc/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"mhc","source_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":1},"text_hash":"24d57bb637428607f5abfe1328896a5079f57131"},{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../gill/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":4}}],"5":[{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../pulpit/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"pulpit","source_name":"Pulpit Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":5}},{"match":"hash","source_href":"../../mhc/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"mhc","source_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":1},"text_hash":"24d57bb637428607f5abfe1328896a5079f57131"},{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../gill/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"gill","source_name":"Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":5}}],"6":[{"match":"direct","source_href":"../../pulpit/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"pulpit","source_name":"Pulpit Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zephaniah","chapter":3,"entry_index":0,"source_chapter":3,"verse":6}},{"match":"hash","source_href":"../../mhc/zephaniah/3.htm","source_id":"mhc","source_name":"Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary","source_ref":{"book_id":"zepha